I know I grind my teeth at night. I used to wake up with terrible headaches from it. At my last dentist appointment, I got a mouthguard. It protects my teeth, but it doesn't help with the issue I have. In fact, I feel like some ways it causes me to grind harder because the sensation of the grinding on the mouthguard feels satisfying. 


I find that sometimes even when I'm awake, I'm clenching my jaw so tight and I don't even realise I'm doing it. It happens often enough and I don't necessarily need to be doing something stressful to notice I'm doing it. 


Is there anything I can do for this besides just wearing a mouthguard at night? Any idea why this could be happening?

Thanks! :)
